Subject: [PATCH] Linux: link the complete static libc++ closure

Nucleus builds and installs libc++, libc++abi, and LLVM libunwind and configures
Clang to use libc++ by default. Swift's upstream Linux static-executable
response file names libstdc++, which Clang consequently translates to libc++
without adding the separately built ABI and unwind archives. Fully static
Swift executables then fail with unresolved C++ ABI symbols. FoundationXML's
autolinked static libxml2 dependency also requires zlib. Encode both transitive
closures in the installed response file so `swiftc -static-executable` works
without caller-supplied linker flags.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_LINUX_STATIC_LIBCXX_CLOSURE

diff --git a/stdlib/public/Resources/linux/static-executable-args.lnk b/stdlib/public/Resources/linux/static-executable-args.lnk
index 7b1094ebdcf..270a7e7b8a2 100644
--- a/stdlib/public/Resources/linux/static-executable-args.lnk
+++ b/stdlib/public/Resources/linux/static-executable-args.lnk
@@ -11,5 +11,8 @@
 -lBlocksRuntime
 -lpthread
 -ldl
--lstdc++
+-lc++
+-lc++abi
+-lunwind
 -lm
+-lz
